# strix-milter environment. systemd reads this via EnvironmentFile.
# Full reference: README.md "Milter (Postfix / Sendmail)".

# --- the strixd to scan with (REQUIRED) ---
# Base URL of the strixd daemon. The milter links no YARA and holds no rules; it
# POSTs each message here and stamps the answer as a header.
MAILSTRIX_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8079

# --- the milter socket the MTA connects to ---
# inet:HOST:PORT or unix:/path/to.sock. Keep it on loopback (or a unix socket):
# anyone who can reach this port can have messages scanned.
#MAILSTRIX_MILTER_LISTEN=inet:127.0.0.1:8081

# --- shared secret ---
# The token strixd requires (MAILSTRIX_TOKEN there). Leave unset for a
# token-less strixd. Prefer -token-file in ExecStart over putting the secret
# here if this file is readable by more than the service account.
#MAILSTRIX_TOKEN=

# --- extra flags ---
# Appended to ExecStart. Useful ones:
#   -timeout 20s      hard per-message deadline; on expiry the message is
#                     ACCEPTED with an unknown verdict (mail is never blocked)
#   -max-body 8388608 messages larger than this are accepted UNSCANNED rather
#                     than scanned as a truncated prefix (which would be a
#                     silent miss)
#   -log-clean        log clean verdicts too (noisy)
#MAILSTRIX_MILTER_ARGS=
